## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 Class Structure Block Diagram (Mermaid)

The following Mermaid block illustrates the **internal anatomy** of a Java class as taught in KTU Module 2.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["JAVA CLASS: Student"] --> B["1. FIELDS (State)"]
    A --> C["2. CONSTRUCTORS (Initialisation)"]
    A --> D["3. METHODS (Behaviour)"]
    A --> E["4. ACCESS MODIFIERS"]

    B --> B1["private String name"]
    B --> B2["private int rollNo"]
    B --> B3["private double cgpa"]

    C --> C1["public Student() - no-arg"]
    C --> C2["public Student(String, int, double) - parameterised"]

    D --> D1["public void display()"]
    D --> D2["public boolean isEligible()"]
    D --> D3["public String getName()"]
    D --> D4["public void setCgpa(double)"]

    E --> E1["public - visible everywhere"]
    E --> E2["private - within class only"]
    E --> E3["protected - package and subclasses"]
    E --> E4["default - same package"]
```

### 4.2 Class-to-Object Instantiation Flow

This diagram shows how a class is converted into runtime objects (the most-asked KTU diagram).

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["CLASS Student<br/>Blueprint in .java file"] -->|Compile: javac| B[".class file<br/>Bytecode"]
    B -->|JVM loads| C["Method Area<br/>Class metadata"]
    C -->|new Student Anu| D["Heap Memory<br/>Object 1 s1"]
    C -->|new Student Ravi| E["Heap Memory<br/>Object 2 s2"]
    C -->|new Student Meera| F["Heap Memory<br/>Object 3 s3"]
    D --> G["Stack: s1 = ref"]
    E --> H["Stack: s2 = ref"]
    F --> I["Stack: s3 = ref"]
```

### 4.3 UML-Style Class Diagram (Mermaid)

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class Student {
        -String name
        -int rollNo
        -double cgpa
        +Student()
        +Student(String, int, double)
        +getName() String
        +setCgpa(double) void
        +display() void
        +isEligible() boolean
    }
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Legend used:**
> `-` denotes **private** access
> `+` denotes **public** access
> This is the **standard UML notation** KTU expects in your answer sheets.

### 4.4 Access Modifier Visibility Matrix (Conceptual Diagram)

```mermaid
graph TD
    P["public"] --> ALL["Visible EVERYWHERE"]
    PR["protected"] --> P1["Same Package"]
    PR --> P2["Subclasses outside package"]
    D["default (no keyword)"] --> P1
    PV["private"] --> SC["Same CLASS only"]
```

