> **High-Density Rapid Revision Checklist for KTU 2024 Exam**

### `final` Keyword
- ☐ `final` variable = constant, assigned exactly **once** (compiler error on second assignment)
- ☐ `final` method = **cannot be overridden** in any subclass
- ☐ `final` class = **cannot be inherited** (no subclass possible)
- ☐ `final` on **reference** freezes the reference, NOT the object's state
- ☐ Naming convention for `static final` constants: `ALL_CAPS_WITH_UNDERSCORES`
- ☐ `String`, all wrapper classes (`Integer`, `Double`), and `java.lang.Math` are `final`
- ☐ A `final` method allows JIT optimization via inlining

### Packages
- ☐ Package = **logical namespace** + **physical folder** (both must match)
- ☐ Reverse-domain naming: `com.company.project`
- ☐ `package` declaration is the **first statement** in a Java file
- ☐ `import` is used to access classes from other packages
- ☐ `java.lang` is **auto-imported**; no explicit import needed for `String`, `System`
- ☐ `import static` is used for static members (e.g., `Math.PI`)
- ☐ **CLASSPATH** = path where compiler/JVM looks for user-defined packages
- ☐ Default (package-private) access = same package only

### Interfaces
- ☐ Interface = 100% abstract contract (pre-Java 8) + default/static methods (Java 8+)
- ☐ Interface variables are implicitly `public static final` (constants only)
- ☐ Interface methods are implicitly `public abstract` (unless `default` or `static`)
- ☐ Interfaces **cannot** have constructors and **cannot** be instantiated
- ☐ Class uses `implements` to fulfil an interface
- ☐ Interface uses `extends` to inherit another interface
- ☐ A class can **implement multiple interfaces** (multiple inheritance of type)
- ☐ A class can extend **only one** class (single inheritance of state)
- ☐ **Default method** = concrete method in interface (backward compatibility)
- ☐ **Static method** in interface called via `InterfaceName.method()`
- ☐ **Diamond problem** resolution: implementing class **must override** conflicting default methods
- ☐ Use `InterfaceName.super.method()` to call specific inherited default method
- ☐ Java 9+ allows `private` methods in interfaces (helper methods for defaults)

### Common Pitfalls to Avoid in KTU Exam
- ❌ Writing `extends` instead of `implements` for a class
- ❌ Writing `implements` instead of `extends` between two interfaces
- ❌ Forgetting the folder structure matches the package name
- ❌ Confusing `default` access (package) with `protected` (package + subclasses)
- ❌ Trying to instantiate an interface (e.g., `new MyInterface();`)
- ❌ Overriding a `final` method (compile-time error)
- ❌ Extending a `final` class (compile-time error)
- ❌ Using `super.method()` instead of `InterfaceName.super.method()` to call default method
