### 3.3 Worked Example 3 — Unreachable Code Compilation Error

**Problem:** Identify the compile-time error.

```java
try {
    int x = 10 / 0;
}
catch (Exception e) {                 // Generic handler first
    System.out.println("Generic");
}
catch (ArithmeticException e) {        // Subclass — UNREACHABLE
    System.out.println("Arithmetic");
}
```

**Compiler Diagnostic:**

```
error: exception java.lang.ArithmeticException has already been caught
       catch (ArithmeticException e) {
       ^
```

**Resolution:** Swap the order so that the more specific `ArithmeticException` precedes `Exception`.
