## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 Control-Flow Diagram — Try-Catch Cascade

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Program enters try block] --> B{Statement executes}
    B -->|No exception| C[Skip all catch blocks]
    B -->|Exception thrown| D{JVM constructs exception object}
    D --> E[Search catch 1: type match?]
    E -->|Yes| F1[Execute catch 1 handler]
    E -->|No| G[Search catch 2: type match?]
    G -->|Yes| F2[Execute catch 2 handler]
    G -->|No| H[More catch blocks?]
    H -->|Yes| E
    H -->|No| I[No match - propagate to caller]
    F1 --> J[Execute finally block if present]
    F2 --> J
    C --> J
    I --> K[Unhandled exception - JVM terminates]
    J --> L[Continue after try-catch-finally]
```

### 4.2 Exception Class Hierarchy (Block Architecture)

```mermaid
graph TD
    OBJ[java.lang.Object] --> THR[java.lang.Throwable]
    THR --> ERR[java.lang.Error]
    THR --> EXC[java.lang.Exception]
    EXC --> IOE[java.io.IOException]
    EXC --> SQE[java.sql.SQLException]
    EXC --> RTE[java.lang.RuntimeException]
    RTE --> AE[ArithmeticException]
    RTE --> NPE[NullPointerException]
    RTE --> AIOOBE[ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException]
    RTE --> NFE[NumberFormatException]
