#### Model Solution for (b):

```java
class Worker extends Thread {
    private volatile boolean suspended = false;

    public void suspendWork() {
        suspended = true;
    }

    public synchronized void resumeWork() {
        suspended = false;
        notify();
    }

    public void run() {
        for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
            try {
                synchronized (this) {
                    while (suspended) {
                        System.out.println("Thread paused at i=" + i);
                        wait();
                    }
                }
                System.out.println("Working: " + i);
                Thread.sleep(300);
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                System.out.println("Interrupted");
            }
        }
    }
}

public class SuspendDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Worker w = new Worker();
        w.start();
        Thread.sleep(800);
        w.suspendWork();
        Thread.sleep(1500);
        w.resumeWork();
    }
}
```

**Explanation of Code (7 marks breakdown):**
- `volatile boolean suspended` — ensures flag visibility (1 mark)
- `suspendWork()` sets flag = true (1 mark)
- `resumeWork()` resets flag and calls `notify()` (1 mark)
- `synchronized(this)` + `while(suspended)` + `wait()` — proper guarded wait (2 marks)
