## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes Where Students Lose Marks:**
> 1. **Forgetting `volatile` on the flag:** Examiners deduct 1 mark if the boolean flag is not declared `volatile`. The Java Memory Model is a tested concept.
> 2. **Using `if` instead of `while` for the wait condition:** Always use `while(suspended) wait();` — `if` is vulnerable to **spurious wakeups** and is a classic KTU board trap. Loss: 2 marks.
> 3. **Calling `wait()` outside a `synchronized` block:** This throws `IllegalMonitorStateException` at runtime. Examiners test for this. Loss: 1 mark.
> 4. **Writing only theoretical answer without code for the 7-mark part:** KTU 2024 strictly requires a working program for the "demonstrate" sub-question.
> 5. **Confusing `sleep()` with `wait()`:** They are **not** interchangeable. `sleep()` does not release locks; `wait()` does.

