# Section 2: Deep Theoretical Analysis & KTU High-Yield Cheat Sheet

## 2.1 Event Class Hierarchy (The Complete Chain)

The Java event classes follow a strict inheritance hierarchy. Understanding this hierarchy is **high-yield for KTU board examinations** because examiners frequently ask students to "draw and explain the event class hierarchy."

```
java.util.EventObject                       (Root)
        │
        └── java.awt.AWTEvent               (AWT-specific root)
                │
                ├── ActionEvent             (Button click, menu selection)
                ├── ItemEvent               (Checkbox, list item toggle)
                ├── AdjustmentEvent         (Scrollbar movement)
                ├── TextEvent               (Text field changes)
                │
                └── ComponentEvent
                        ├── PaintEvent
                        ├── WindowEvent
                        ├── FocusEvent
                        └── ContainerEvent
                                └── InputEvent
                                        ├── KeyEvent
                                        └── MouseEvent
                                                └── MouseWheelEvent
```

## 2.2 Detailed Breakdown of Each Major Event Class

### **A. ActionEvent** (`java.awt.event.ActionEvent`)
- **Generated by**: `Button`, `MenuItem`, `TextField` (on Enter), `JButton`, `JMenuItem`.
- **Event ID constant**: `ACTION_PERFORMED` (integer value **1001**).
- **Purpose**: Fires when a user performs a "command action" — clicking a button or selecting a menu.
- **Key methods**: `getActionCommand()`, `getModifiers()`.

### **B. ItemEvent** (`java.awt.event.ItemEvent`)
- **Generated by**: `Checkbox`, `CheckboxMenuItem`, `Choice`, `List`.
- **Event ID constants**: `ITEM_STATE_CHANGED` (**701**).
- **Purpose**: Fires when an item's selection state changes (checked ↔ unchecked, selected ↔ deselected).
- **Key methods**: `getItem()`, `getItemSelectable()`, `getStateChange()`.
- **State constants**: `SELECTED`, `DESELECTED`.

### **C. KeyEvent** (`java.awt.event.KeyEvent`)
- **Generated by**: Any focus-holding component when a key is pressed, released, or typed.
- **Event ID constants**: `KEY_PRESSED` (**401**), `KEY_RELEASED` (**402**), `KEY_TYPED` (**400**).
- **Key methods**: `getKeyChar()`, `getKeyCode()`, `getKeyText()`, `isActionKey()`, `getModifiersEx()`.
- **Special**: Extends `InputEvent`, which extends `ComponentEvent`.

### **D. MouseEvent** (`java.awt.event.MouseEvent`)
- **Generated by**: Any component under the mouse cursor.
- **Event ID constants**: `MOUSE_CLICKED` (**5001**), `MOUSE_PRESSED` (**5002**), `MOUSE_RELEASED** (**5003**), `MOUSE_ENTERED` (**5004**), `MOUSE_EXITED** (**5005**).
- **Key methods**: `getX()`, `getY()`, `getPoint()`, `getClickCount()`, `getButton()`, `isPopupTrigger()`.

### **E. WindowEvent** (`java.awt.event.WindowEvent`)
- **Generated by**: `Window` and its subclasses (`Frame`, `Dialog`).
- **Event ID constants**: `WINDOW_OPENED`, `WINDOW_CLOSING`, `WINDOW_CLOSED`, `WINDOW_ICONIFIED`, `WINDOW_DEICONIFIED`, `WINDOW_ACTIVATED`, `WINDOW_DEACTIVATED`.
- **Key methods**: `getWindow()`, `getOppositeWindow()`.

### **F. AdjustmentEvent** (`java.awt.event.AdjustmentEvent`)
- **Generated by**: `Scrollbar`.
- **Key methods**: `getAdjustable()`, `getAdjustmentType()`, `getValue()`, `getAdjustmentType()` returns one of: `UNIT_INCREMENT`, `UNIT_DECREMENT`, `BLOCK_INCREMENT`, `BLOCK_DECREMENT`, `TRACK`.

### **G. FocusEvent** (`java.awt.event.FocusEvent`)
- **Generated by**: Any `Component` gaining or losing keyboard focus.
- **Key methods**: `isTemporary()`, `getOppositeComponent()`.

### **H. TextEvent** (`java.awt.event.TextEvent`)
- **Generated by**: `TextField`, `TextArea` when text changes.
- **Event ID**: `TEXT_VALUE_CHANGED`.
- **Key method**: Inherits `getSource()` only — text value retrieved from source.

### **I. ComponentEvent** (`java.awt.event.ComponentEvent`)
- **Superclass** of most spatial events.
- **Event IDs**: `COMPONENT_MOVED`, `COMPONENT_RESIZED`, `COMPONENT_SHOWN`, `COMPONENT_HIDDEN`.
- **Key method**: `getComponent()`.

### **J. ContainerEvent** (`java.awt.event.ContainerEvent`)
- **Generated by**: `Container` when a child component is added/removed.
- **Key methods**: `getChild()`, `getContainer()`.

### **K. PaintEvent** (`java.awt.event.PaintEvent`)
- **Internal use** — rarely handled by user code.

## 2.3 KTU High-Yield Cheat Sheet

| Event Class | Source Components | Listener Interface | Key Accessor Methods |
|-------------|-------------------|---------------------|-----------------------|
| `ActionEvent` | `Button`, `MenuItem` | `ActionListener` | `getActionCommand()`, `getModifiers()` |
| `ItemEvent` | `Checkbox`, `List` | `ItemListener` | `getItem()`, `getStateChange()` |
