## 2.4 Engineering Utility

> [!NOTE]
> **Real-World Engineering Application:**
> Event classes form the backbone of every interactive software system — from **ATM interfaces** (ActionEvent for key presses, WindowEvent for card insertion screens) to **industrial SCADA dashboards** (MouseEvent for operator clicks, AdjustmentEvent for threshold sliders). In **embedded systems** with Java ME, KeyEvent drives hardware keypad input. In **robotics control GUIs**, MouseEvent and KeyEvent provide real-time teleoperation feedback.

