**Model Answer:**

An **event class** is a Java class in the `java.awt.event` package that encapsulates state information about an event generated by a GUI component. It provides accessor methods to retrieve details like the source, event type, time, and coordinates.

The root class of all AWT event classes is **`java.util.EventObject`**, with `java.awt.AWTEvent` being the AWT-specific root.

