## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!NOTE]
> **Rapid Revision Checklist for Event Classes:**
>
> ☐ **Root class** is `java.util.EventObject`; **AWT root** is `java.awt.AWTEvent`.
>
> ☐ **11 primary event classes** exist: ActionEvent, ItemEvent, AdjustmentEvent, TextEvent, ComponentEvent, PaintEvent, WindowEvent, FocusEvent, ContainerEvent, KeyEvent, MouseEvent (plus MouseWheelEvent).
>
> ☐ Every event class provides **`getSource()`** (from EventObject) and **`getID()`** (from AWTEvent) at minimum.
>
> ☐ **Event IDs are integer constants**: `ACTION_PERFORMED = 1001`, `MOUSE_CLICKED = 500`, `KEY_PRESSED = 401`, `ITEM_STATE_CHANGED = 701`.
>
> ☐ **ActionEvent** carries: `getActionCommand()`, `getModifiers()`, `getWhen()`.
>
> ☐ **MouseEvent** carries: `getX()`, `getY()`, `getPoint()`, `getClickCount()`, `getButton()`.
>
> ☐ **KeyEvent** carries: `getKeyChar()`, `getKeyCode()`, `getKeyText()`, `isActionKey()`.
>
> ☐ **WindowEvent** carries: `getWindow()`, `getOppositeWindow()`.
>
> ☐ **ItemEvent** carries: `getItem()`, `getStateChange()` (returns `SELECTED` or `DESELECTED`).
>
> ☐ **AdjustmentEvent** carries: `getValue()`, `getAdjustable()`, `getAdjustmentType()`.
>
> ☐ **FocusEvent** carries: `isTemporary()`, `getOppositeComponent()`.
>
> ☐ **ContainerEvent** carries: `getChild()`, `getContainer()`.
>
> ☐ The **Delegation Event Model** has 4 participants: Source, Event Class, Listener Interface, Handler Method.
>
> ☐ Event source must call **`addXxxListener(listenerObject)`** to register listeners.
>
> ☐ Multiple listeners can be registered to **one source**; one listener can handle **many sources**.
>
> ☐ Keyboard events only fire on components with **focus** — call `setFocusable(true)`.
>
> ☐ **Package path**: All event classes live in **`java.awt.event`** package.
>
> ☐ For KTU 14-mark questions: always include the **hierarchy diagram** + at least **3 event classes explained** + **one working program** demonstrating event class usage.

